title: The triumphs of London prepared for the entertaiment [sic] of the right honorable Sir Thomas Lane, knight, Lord Mayor of the city of London. Containing a full description of the pageants, speeches, songs, and the whole solemnity of the day. Performed one Monday the 29 of October, 1694. Set forth at the proper cost and charges of the honorable Company of Clothworkers. Published by authority.
author: Settle, Elkanah, 1648-1724.
publisher: printed and are to be sold by Richard Baldwin, at the Oxford Arms Inn, in Warwick-Lane,
